    "The γ > 0 is used to control the contribution of hard and easy samples, which reduces the impact of easy samples and focus more on positive and negative hard samples.",
    "The α t controls the weight of positive and negative samples.",
    "Contrastive LearningIn the self-supervised domain, contrastive learning aims to pull together an anchor and a \"positive\" sample and push apart the anchor from many \"negative\" samples in embedding space.",
    "In order to model the differences between different source samples, we need to construct a Contrastive loss.",
    "We will refer to a set of N samples as a \"batch\" and 2N augmented samples for the batch as I."
